The paper proposes a neural architecture for detecting off-topic responses to visual prompts, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
